To implement the shopping cart aggregate root in C++17 using CRTP (Curiously Recurring Template Pattern) and the visitor pattern, you can follow these steps:

1. **Define the base class for the shopping cart:**

Create a base class for the shopping cart using CRTP. This class will provide a common interface for all shopping cart implementations.

```cpp
// ShoppingCart.h
#pragma once
#include <memory>
#include <vector>

template <typename Derived>
class ShoppingCart {
public:
    using Id = std::string;

    virtual ~ShoppingCart() = default;

    Id getId() const { return id_; }
    const std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Derived>>& getItems() const { return items_; }

    void addItem(const std::shared_ptr<Derived>& item) { items_.push_back(item); }

    virtual void accept(class ShoppingCartVisitor& visitor) = 0;

protected:
    ShoppingCart(Id id) : id_(std::move(id)) {}

private:
    Id id_;
    std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Derived>> items_;
};
```

2. **Define the shopping cart item:**

Create a shopping cart item class that inherits from the base shopping cart class using CRTP. This class will represent the items in the shopping cart.

```cpp
// ShoppingCartItem.h
#pragma once
#include "ShoppingCart.h"

class ShoppingCartItem : public ShoppingCart<ShoppingCartItem> {
public:
    using ShoppingCart<ShoppingCartItem>::ShoppingCart;

    void accept(class ShoppingCartVisitor& visitor) override {
        visitor.visit(*this);
    }
};
```

3. **Define the shopping cart visitor:**

Create a shopping cart visitor class that will be used to traverse the shopping cart items and perform operations on them.

```cpp
// ShoppingCartVisitor.h
#pragma once
#include "ShoppingCartItem.h"

class ShoppingCartVisitor {
public:
    virtual void visit(ShoppingCartItem& item) = 0;
};
```

4. **Implement the shopping cart visitor:**

Create a concrete implementation of the shopping cart visitor that performs the desired operations on the shopping cart items.

```cpp
// ShoppingCartTotalVisitor.h
#pragma once
#include "ShoppingCartVisitor.h"
#include "Money.h"

class ShoppingCartTotalVisitor : public ShoppingCartVisitor {
public:
    void visit(ShoppingCartItem& item) override {
        total_ += item.getTotal();
    }

    Money getTotal() const { return total_; }

private:
    Money total_;
};
```

5. **Use the shopping cart aggregate root:**

Now you can use the shopping cart aggregate root with the visitor pattern to perform operations on the shopping cart items.

```cpp
// main.cpp
#include "ShoppingCartItem.h"
#include "ShoppingCartTotalVisitor.h"

int main() {
    // Create a shopping cart
    auto cart = std::make_shared<ShoppingCartItem>("cart-id");

    // Add items to the shopping cart
    cart->addItem(std::make_shared<ShoppingCartItem>("item-1"));
    cart->addItem(std::make_shared<ShoppingCartItem>("item-2"));

    // Calculate the total of the shopping cart using the visitor pattern
    ShoppingCartTotalVisitor visitor;
    for (const auto& item : cart->getItems()) {
        item->accept(visitor);
    }
    Money total = visitor.getTotal();

    // Print the total
    std::cout << "Total: " << total << std::endl;

    return 0;
}
```

By following these steps, you can implement the shopping cart aggregate root in C++17 using CRTP and the visitor pattern. This approach allows you to encapsulate the behavior of the shopping cart items and perform operations on them using the visitor pattern.

